      <h1>Getting Started with Crochet</h1>
      <img src="images/crochet-tools.jpg" alt="Crochet hook and yarn" class="responsive-img">
      <p>Learning to crochet starts with gathering the right tools and understanding some basic techniques. Follow this step-by-step guide to begin your crochet journey!</p>

      <h2 id="tools">Tools You Need</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Crochet hook (size H/8 is great for beginners)</li>
        <li>Worsted weight yarn</li>
        <li>Scissors</li>
        <li>Yarn needle</li>
        <li>Stitch markers (optional)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Basic Crochet Stitches</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Slip Knot</li>
        <li>Chain Stitch (ch)</li>
        <li>Single Crochet (sc)</li>
        <li>Double Crochet (dc)</li>
        <li>Half Double Crochet (hdc)</li>
      </ol>

      <p>Practice these stitches to build your skills. Refer to tutorials or diagrams as needed. Once youâ€™re confident, you can try making small projects like dishcloths or scarves.</p>

